

<section xml:id="chap9probs">
  <title>Practice</title>
  <p>
    We will not present the problems from this section, although you are welcome to ask about them in class.
  </p>

  <p>
    <em>Cross Products</em>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Compute the cross product of <m>\oa u = (3,2,-1)</m> and <m>\oa v = (2,\pi,-3)</m> and state the significance of the resulting vector.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Find two vectors of unit length orthogonal to both <m>\oa a = (4,-3,2)</m> and <m>\oa b = (2,5,-3).</m>
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    <em>Planes</em>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Find the equation of a plane parallel to <m>3x +2z = 4 - y</m> and containing <m>(2,4,-2).</m>
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Find the equation of the line that represents the intersection of <m>3z - 4x + 2y = 4</m> and <m>2z - x = 6 - y.</m>
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Find an equation for the plane containing <m>(1,2,3), (2,3,4),</m> and <m>(-1,1,1).</m>  Find another equation for the same plane.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Find the distance between the two planes: <m>2x-3y+5z=5</m> and <m>2x-3y+5z=15</m>.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    <em>Limits</em>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Consider the function defined by
          <m>f(x,y)=\left\{ \begin{array}{ll}
          \dsp{\frac{x^2}{x^2+y}} \amp  x^2+y \neq 0\\
          0 \amp  (x,y)=(0,0)
          \end{array}  \right.</m>

          Does the limit exist as <m>(x,y) \to (0,0)</m> along <m>y=kx</m> exist for every <m>k \in \re?</m>  Does the limit exist as <m>(x,y) \to (0,0)</m> along <m>y=kx^2</m> exist for every <m>k \in \re?</m> Is the function <m>f</m> continuous at <m>(x,y)=(0,0)</m>?
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

