  <p>
    <em>Limits</em>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          No, for a chosen value of <m>k</m>, the limit along the path
          <m>y=kx^2</m> would be <m>\frac{1}{1+k}.</m>  Therefore the limit along
          different parabolic paths (different values of <m>k</m>) would
          yield different results.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
